What is an EJS Layout?

In EJS (Embedded JavaScript), a layout is a common template file that contains the shared structure of your pages — like:

<html>, <head>, <body>

Navbar

Sidebar

Footer

CSS & JS links

Instead of repeating this structure in every page (dashboard, users, login, etc.), you create one layout file and inject page-specific content into it.

